<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=48582#M48582">2</a> of 66
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2694 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>Klonn_Darkbane's reply, cut from the other thread and pasted here.</P>
<P>
<HR>
Nolrog wrote:</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Klonn_Darkbane wrote:<BR>
<DIV>I am starting a new thread on the Grouping options just so the discussion does not get lost here.
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>I noticed that.&nbsp; I was going to add something, but my thoughts are more solo orientated (specifically on the task system), so they don't belong there.&nbsp; I'll add them here instead, and then move to a new thread of warranted.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV>
<DIV>Improvements to the task system:<BR>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>All the rewards I've seen to date have been XP and coin.&nbsp; I'd suggest other types of rewards, such as significant faction hits for hard to raise factions after a long task (such as Freeport Militia); possibly item rewards based on a need you have (you could make the person specifically pick the task he wanted based on the reward he needs.)&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Ideally, the system should check to see if you have the key to a certain zone, before giving you the task for it.&nbsp; Alternatively, you should see the keys required for the task, so you could accept or decline based on that.&nbsp; Another suggestion is to temporarily key someone for the zone while they are doing the step in the task that needs it (but this is open to a bit of abuse.)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>XP rewards for completing a task&nbsp;should be increased as an incentive to do them.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Add back in the PoP tasks that were removed because they were too hard.&nbsp; Give them a super hard rating, and allow the rewards to be given accordingly.&nbsp; Some people might grab a friend to do that task, or both get the task so they could do it together.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Allow people within the same level to get the same task, so they can do it together.&nbsp; There was one time that friend and I (forgot what class we were each playing, but it wasn't the same) were looking to do the same task, so we could group up and do it together.&nbsp; We weren't exactly the same level, but we were only a level or two apart.&nbsp; We looked and looked but never did find the same task.&nbsp; We wound up getting one that, from the title, appeared to send us to Mistmoore (it did.)&nbsp; However, his task was a lot harder than mine.&nbsp; We completed mine, and not his.&nbsp; I think that was the last time he attempted a task.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Allow tasks to be given out from any task master.&nbsp; It's a royal PitA to have to run to DL to get a task, because you're over 30 (or whatever the level cutoff is.)&nbsp; Also fix the taskmasters.&nbsp; Sometimes, I'd be within the level range, and at the correct taskmaster, and they still wouldn't give me a task.&nbsp; I had to repeatedly hail them before they'd give it to me.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The tasks I've done, concentrated on old world and Kunark.&nbsp; I haven't seen any in other expansions (though I understand the low level Vah Shir ones take you to Hollowshade and the like.)&nbsp; Add in tasks from other expansions, so there's a little more variety.&nbsp; Even tasks that take you to more than one expansion (I think it's time for the whole each expansion must be a separate entity idea to be partially done away with.)&nbsp; I'd love to see a task that gave out a nice reward&nbsp;for collecting something within all the LDoN dungeons (perhaps even bonus LDoN points).&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Retune the tasks, so they are more appropriate for the class/level.&nbsp; I got one that asked&nbsp;my enchanter (level 51) to kill 10 wyverns in Skyfire.&nbsp; That was impossible to do solo (had to get help from a necro friend.)</DIV>
<DIV></FONT></DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>Great ideas and I'd suggest moving it to a new thread.</P>
<P>Additional thoughts...</P>
<P>Alternate rewards are a great idea...</P>
<P>Tasks related to your RACE... Reward might be additional personal Tribute points, since your home city "appreciates" the task that you performed for them.</P>
<P>Tasks related to Tradeskills (hehe, you ARE the TS rep, right?). If I deliver MOLDS, for example, from PoK to a smithing vendor in Abysmal Sea, maybe I get 10 points in Blacksmithing (up to a max skill of, say, 50). To prevent misuse, do not allow the same task to be done more than once and put caps on how high any such reward can take you.</P>
<P>Tasks related to CLASS that reward training points.</P>
<P>Tasks related to specific skills that improve that skill (similar to the Tradeskill one above - with the same restrictions). For example, "Lush XYZ in the Freeport Bar has been bad mouthing our organization and needs to be taken down a notch. If you would beat him in a drinking contest, we can show you how to improve your tolerance for alcohol".</P>
<P>Language oriented ones (along the same lines). Deliever a message, in the proper language, to so_and_so.</P>
<P>Comsumables rewards. Bone Chips for SK's and Necros. Stat food &amp; drink for everybody. Potions. NO RENT items galore. LORE, NO DROP, one shot items that are very rare (VoQ or Virtue potions?).</P>
<P>It has been mentioned on other posts that LDoN AP's might be a good reward (but fitting it into backstory might not be possible).</P></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Nolrog Strongbow - 65th season Ranger of Tunare - Drinal<br><a href="http://qff.jettastarr.com" target="_blank">Quest For Fellowship</a><br>Tamox - 35th season ShadowKnight of Innoruuk - The Combine<br><a href="http://www.noxiousguild.org">Noxious</a><br><br>Sarcasm is a service that I happily (and often) provide.<br>
							</div>
								
