			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Nolrog wrote:<BR><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Klonn wrote:<BR><BR>It has been mentioned on other posts that LDoN AP's might be a good reward (but fitting it into backstory might not be possible).<BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>Have the tasks for the LDoNs be given out at the Wayfarer camps.&nbsp; This way, you'd still be doing work for them, but now in the context of a task that spans different adventure themes, rather than doing work for them in an adventure.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>Could even take the "Hill Street Blues" view of the Story Arc... (ok, that is a very obscure reference <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>)</P>
<P>Get the task to collect these 5 things that are semi-rare drops in various LDoN dungeons. Can't do them all at once. Gotta do the LDoN's and watch for those items. </P>
<P>I think you should be able to have more than one Task at a time and there should be no time limit&nbsp;(perhaps 2 levels?). Thus, you obtain the task and can do it on your own time, when you have the time. </P>
<P>This borders on questing, but I do not really see a need to keep them totally separate.</P>
