		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			With LDoN having less and less people, I really love the idea of doing tasks for points.  There's still a lot of things from there I'd like to get.<br><br>I would think you'd have to have one taskmaster per camp, and would get your points for that particular camp.  I would also think that you would not get as many points doing a task as you would doing an adventure.  And there's the whole time issue that needs to be thought about.  Do you have to get the task done in "X" minutes?  That gives porters and fast runners (shamen and bards) an advantage.  I *really* like this idea, but there's a lot to consider before it gets implemented.<br><br>Did I mention I really like this idea?  <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0>	
