		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Suggestions for Improvements to the task system:<br><br>- Place Taskmasters in Thurgadin, Skyshrine, Katta Castellum, Sanctus Seru, Broken Shores of Natimbi, Dranik's Scar, and  Gulf of Gunthak.<br><br>- Taskmasters should check a player's keyring before offering a task. (Been said before, but bears repeating.)<br><br>- LDON Points for Tasks is a Good Thing(tm), especially now that OOW drops outclass most LDON items.<br><br>- Add an option for players to see zones involved in tasks before accepting them. Therefore if a player doesn't want to ruin his Chardok faction, he can turn down Chardok tasks ahead of time, etc...<br><br>- Add an option to be rewarded in terms of tradeskill items rather than cash or experience. I'd task for a chance at slugworms or trean flies if I could. The NPC might give me roots or vegetables, but there's still a chance that I can obtain those tradeskill items.<br><br><br>Suggestions for Soloing -<br><br>- NPC Healers/Bards in city zones ala Galadorian Visigothe.<br><br>- NPC Rezzers/Corpse Summoners, possibly based on the Tribute system.<br><br>- Group invites/summons across zones. (This primarily aids groups, but also aids soloers to a great deal since they can still be invited when they're off in the boonies and don't have to sit in the POK.)<br><br>- Removing or soften existing level caps on crowd control effects like lull, mez, fear, and stun for soloing casters.<br><br>- Faction-specific NPCs in city zones that cast invisibility, perhaps on a tribute basis.
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<hr><font size=-3 color="#666666">The less-organized group of 'casual' monkies are left wondering what's wrong. The levers are now so difficult to push, they're left eating the crumbs of old cookies and whatever comes flying across the room. The only time a Jolly Rancher comes their way, it's already covered in spit and monkey-hair. They're hungry. And their teeth hurt. They need their vitamins and some sweet monkey lovin', but the stench from the 'hard-core' side of the lab makes it difficult to get romantic.<br><br>Good God, won't somone give the casual monkies some dental floss?!</font>
