shadowwv wrote:<BR><BR><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Elmer_The_Fudd wrote:<BR><BR>
<DIV>Everyone getting agro reduction on epics, why?, cause heavy healing, dotting, nuking DPS causes a mob to summon a PC .</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>Elmer, I haven't seen the druid 2.0 effect yet but the 1.5 effect, Nature's Blight (<A href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=6237&amp;source=Live" target=_blank>http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=6237&amp;source=Live</A>) at this time does not have any aggro reduction.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>And I concur with you entirely on the topic of summoning mobs.&nbsp; The proliferation of them is a detriment not only to those that may want to solo but also to many who duo or play in 3-4 person groups.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>You're looking at the wrong effect on the druid 1.5. Try looking here:</P>
<P><A href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=6253" target=_blank>http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=6253</A></P>
<P>There is your aggro reduction.</P>
